@startuml seq_16_participate_in_poll
title Sequence Diagram: UC-16 Participate in Poll

actor User
participant "User Web" as Frontend
participant "Poll Controller" as Controller
participant "Poll Service" as Service
participant "Poll Repo" as PollRepo
participant "Vote Repo" as VoteRepo

User -> Frontend: (1.1) Open a poll post
User -> Frontend: (2.1) Select poll option(s)
User -> Frontend: (3.1) Submit the vote
Frontend -> Controller: (3.2) POST /api/polls/{poll_id}/vote {option_ids}
Controller -> Service: (4.1) Submit poll vote request
Service -> PollRepo: (4.2) Validate authentication and poll state
PollRepo --> Service: (4.3) Poll is valid and open

Service -> VoteRepo: (5.1) Check existing poll vote for user
VoteRepo --> Service: (5.2) Existing vote (if any)

alt Single-choice poll & user already voted
    Service -> VoteRepo: (5.3) Remove prior vote
end

Service -> VoteRepo: (6.1) Record selected poll option(s)
VoteRepo --> Service: (6.2) Vote recorded

Service -> PollRepo: (7.1) Update poll option counters
PollRepo --> Service: (7.2) Counts updated
Service --> Controller: (7.3) Updated poll results
Controller --> Frontend: (7.4) 200 OK
Frontend --> User: (7.5) Display poll results and lock options
@enduml
